      <section eId="sec_CC-802">
        <num>CC 802</num>
        <heading>802.  Right to use the thing</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 802.  Right to use the thing
Except as otherwise provided in Article 801, a co-owner is entitled to use the thing held in indivision according to its destination, but he cannot prevent another co-owner from making such use of it.  As against third persons, a co-owner has the right to use and enjoy the thing as if he were the sole owner.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110998</p>
        </authorialNote>
